    # PMH Wish Fountain dApp - Project Rules

## Project Overview
This is a PMH (Puff Mind Happiness) Wish Fountain decentralized application built for making wishes with PMH tokens. The project is a production-ready Web3 dApp with comprehensive blockchain integration.

## Technical Stack
- **Frontend**: React, Vite, Tailwind CSS
- **Web3**: Multi-L2 blockchain support (Worldchain, Polygon, Arbitrum, Optimism, Base)
- **Authentication**: World ID integration for human verification
- **Wallet Support**: MetaMask, WalletConnect, and other Web3 wallets
- **Monitoring**: Sentry integration for error tracking
- **Build Tool**: Vite with TypeScript support

## Git Configuration
- **Repository**: Connected to https://github.com/Callmix/PMH-builder.git
- **Main Branch**: `main`
- **Git Path**: On Windows, git must be accessed via full path: `& "C:\Program Files\Git\bin\git.exe"`
- **Commit Format**: Always append Memex attribution to commit messages

## Core Features and Business Logic
### PMH Claim Rules
- **Daily Limit**: 3 wishes per 24-hour period
- **Cooldown**: 6 hours between each wish
- **Bonus System**: Extra rewards for completing all 3 daily wishes
- **Character Limit**: Wishes limited to 280 characters
- **History Tracking**: All wishes tracked with timestamps and status (pending, granted, expired)

### Multi-Chain Support
- **Primary Network**: Worldchain (human-verified blockchain)
- **Secondary Networks**: Polygon, Arbitrum, Optimism, Base
- **Chain Switching**: Users can switch between supported L2 networks

### Authentication Flow
- **World ID Verification**: Required for human verification using Worldcoin's IDKit
- **Wallet Connection**: Multi-wallet support with connection state persistence
- **Session Management**: Local storage for persistent state between sessions

## Project Structure Patterns
```
src/components/pmh/ - Core PMH Wish Fountain components
src/components/providers/ - React context providers
src/components/ui/ - Reusable UI components
api/ - Backend API endpoints for verification
```

## Environment Configuration
### Required Environment Variables
- `VITE_WORLDCOIN_APP_ID`: Worldcoin app identifier (required)
- `VITE_WORLDCOIN_API_KEY`: Worldcoin API key (required)
- `VITE_SENTRY_DSN`: Sentry monitoring URL (optional)
- `VITE_WALLETCONNECT_PROJECT_ID`: WalletConnect project ID (optional)
- `VITE_ALCHEMY_API_KEY`: Alchemy API key (optional)

## Development Environment
- **OS**: Windows with PowerShell
- **Node.js**: Version 18+
- **Package Manager**: npm (with package-lock.json present)
- **Dev Server**: Runs on localhost:8080
- **Startup Scripts**: `start.ps1` (Windows) and `start.sh` (Linux/Mac) available

## API Endpoints
### `/api/verify-world-id`
- **Purpose**: Verify World ID proof and authenticate user
- **Method**: POST
- **Required Fields**: merkle_root, nullifier_hash, proof, verification_level

### `/api/minikit-user-grant-cycle`
- **Purpose**: Create grant cycles for PMH token rewards
- **Method**: POST
- **Grant Types**: pmh_bonus, daily_reset, streak_bonus

## UI/UX Patterns
- **Design System**: Purple/blue gradient themes following Apple design guidelines
- **Responsive**: Mobile-first approach
- **Real-time Updates**: Live countdown timers and status updates
- **Error Handling**: Comprehensive error boundaries with user feedback
- **State Management**: Local storage for persistence

    PMH Wish Fountain dApp

    A beautiful, production-ready decentralized application for making wishes with Puff Mind Happiness (PMH) tokens. Built with React, Vite, Tailwind CSS, and Web3 technologies.

    Features

    Core Features

    • Multi-L2 Support: Deploy on Worldchain, Polygon, Arbitrum, Optimism, and Base
    • World ID Integration: Human verification using Worldcoin's IDKit
    • Wallet Connect: Support for MetaMask, WalletConnect, and other Web3 wallets
    • PMH Claim Rules: 3 wishes per day with 6-hour cooldown, bonus after completing all 3
    • Wish History: Track all wishes with status (pending, granted, expired)
    • Statistics Dashboard: View success rates, streaks, and achievements

    Technical Features

    • Production Ready: Sentry monitoring, environment configuration
    • Responsive Design: Mobile-first design with beautiful gradients
    • Real-time Updates: Live countdown timers and status updates
    • Local Storage: Persistent state between sessions
    • Error Handling: Comprehensive error boundaries and user feedback

    Quick Start

    Prerequisites

    • Node.js 18+
    • npm or yarn

    Installation

    1. Clone the repository
      cd PMH-Wish-Fountain
    2. Install dependencies
      npm install
    3. Set up environment variables
      cp .env.example .env.local
      Edit .env.local with your configuration:
      VITE_WORLDCOIN_APP_ID=your_worldcoin_app_id
VITE_WORLDCOIN_API_KEY=your_worldcoin_api_key
VITE_SENTRY_DSN=your_sentry_dsn
VITE_WALLETCONNECT_PROJECT_ID=your_walletconnect_project_id
    4. Start the development server
      npm run dev
      Or use the startup script:
      # Windows
.\start.ps1

# Linux/Mac
./start.sh

    The app will be available at http://localhost:8080

    Usage

    Making Wishes

    1. Connect Wallet: Choose from supported wallets
    2. Verify Identity: Complete World ID verification
    3. Make Wishes: Write your wish (up to 280 characters)
    4. Track Progress: Monitor daily quota (3/3)
    5. Wait for Cooldown: 6-hour wait between wishes
    6. Earn Bonuses: Complete all 3 daily wishes for rewards

    PMH Claim Rules

    • Daily Limit: 3 wishes per 24-hour period
    • Cooldown: 6 hours between each wish
    • Bonus System: Extra rewards for completing all 3 wishes
    • History: All wishes are tracked with timestamps and status

    API Endpoints

    POST /api/verify-world-id

    Verify World ID proof and authenticate user.

    Request:

    {
  "merkle_root": "string",
  "nullifier_hash": "string", 
  "proof": "string",
  "verification_level": "orb" | "device"
}

    Response:

    {
  "verified": true,
  "nullifier_hash": "string"
}

    POST /api/minikit-user-grant-cycle

    Create grant cycles for PMH token rewards.

    Request:

    {
  "user_id": "string",
  "grant_type": "pmh_bonus" | "daily_reset" | "streak_bonus",
  "amount": 100
}
